<HEADLINE>Sober thought</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976764929</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
CHICAGO: Japanese scientists reported that traditional Chinese
medicines such as horse chestnuts, angelica, or camellia seeds seem to
give the capacity to drink without becoming drunk. The medicines appear
to have the ability to grab alcohol and route it through the digestive
system before it can be absorbed into the bloodstream, experts say after
testing the effect on rats.
</TEXT>
