<TEXT>
AN international firm of consulting engineers, transport planners and
environment specialists yesterday announced that it has acquired the
civil engineering design offices of the British Railways Board at
Glasgow and Swindon.
The acquisition will involve about 60 staff at the Infrastructure
Design Group (IDG) in Glasgow and 140 staff at MainLine Swindon Ltd,
coming under the wing of Scott Wilson Kirkpatrick (SWK).
