<DATE>950822</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Sony to link with BBC on digital television</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>27</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976764964</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
JAPAN'S Sony Corporation has agreed to co-operate with the BBC,
British Telecom and other companies to introduce digital terrestrial
television in Britain, Sony confirmed yesterday.
A spokesman for the Japanese electronics conglomerate said other
members of the development group would include US electronics firm
Motorola and Channel 4 and ITV.
''The aim is to develop an open and competitive market in service
provision, receivers and conditional access to ensure rapid
implementation,'' Sony said, adding that the group was open to more
applications for membership.
