<TEXT>
TOKYO: A man lost in the mountains of central Japan survived for a
week by resting under a large rock and eating tadpoles, according to
news reports. Kenshi Sakamoto, who got lost on Mount Misen on Augyst 13,
was found when friends followed a trail of red tape he tied to trees.
