<DATE>950822</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Fake bomb plant</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976764995</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ORLANDO: Dutch authorities planted mock explosives in an unsuspecting
American passenger's luggage to test airport security, it emerged
yesterday. The plant went undetected until the passenger himself, a
university professor, pointed out a rip in his bag. The incident came at
a time when all US airports have heightened security against possible
terrorist acts. Dutch Customs officers have been forbidden to carry out
suc trials in future.
</TEXT>
