<TEXT>
W E THORNLEY should throw away his Concise Oxford (August 18).
Chambers gives both bike and byke for a wasps' nest while the Concise
Scots Dictionary gives byke and boick,
Whatever the spelling, they ar e still rather nasty -- I was stung
twice recently for the first time in my 64 years.
