<DOCID>GH950822-000140</DOCID>
<DATE>950822</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Singer in suicide attempt</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976765069</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Los Angeles
DAVID GAHAN, leader of the top-selling British band Depeche Mode, is
recovering in hospital today after trying to commit suicide.
Police responded to an emergency call at the singer's Los Angeles home
last Thursday and found he had slashed his wrist with a razor blade.
''He sustained a in laceration to his wrist,'' said Detective Joel
Brown. ''It wasn't like he was dying.''
Gahan, 33, is being evaluated for mental competency at Los Angeles'
Cedars Sinai Medical Centre, Brown said.
Depeche Mode, best known for songs such as ''Just Can't Get Enough''
and ''Personal Jesus'', have sold millions of records and packed
stadiums since the early 1980s.--Reuter.
</TEXT>
