<HEADLINE>Actress's lover released</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976765093</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE lover of the EastEnders actress Gillian Taylforth was released on
bail yesterday following a weekend in the cells after claims that he had
disobeyed bail conditions.
Mr Geoffrey Knights was warned to keep away from the actress until his
court case on a charge of assault on her driver, which is expected to
take place in October.
Judge Myrella Cohen, QC, also warned Miss Taylforth not to speak to
the press.
Harrow Crown Court was told that Mr Knights and Miss Taylforth were
photographed by a newspaper outside the BBC's Elstree studios on August
9.
At the time, Mr Knights' bail conditions said that he must not meet
Miss Taylforth.
In court, Miss Taylforth said the meeting occurred only because she
could find no-one to look after the couple's three-year-old daughter,
Jessica.
</TEXT>
