<HEADLINE>Man jailed for raping girl, five</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976765098</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A MAN who raped a five-year-old girl and molested three other young
girls was jailed for eight years yesterday at the High Court in
Edinburgh.
James Smith, 37, of Ness Drive, Arbroath, admitted the rape and using
lewd, indecent, and libidinous practices towards three young girls, aged
12, seven, and eight.
Lord Caplan said Smith's conduct ''was disgusting, dangerous, and has
to be severely discouraged by the court''.
Mr Scott Brady, prosecuting counsel, told the court that matters came
to light when one of the girls went home and told her mother ''something
had happened to her''.
Mr Brady said that some of the indecent assaults took place when Smith
played a game of ''ghosties'' with the younger girls.
Mr Hugh Matthews, QC, defence counsel, said Smith was a man of limited
intelligence who had had an unhappy childhood and had been the victim of
abuse as a young boy.
Mr Matthews claimed Smith had been subjected to terrible treatment
while on remand.
Because he had been charged with sexual offences against young girls,
other prisoners threw urine and scalding water over him.
</TEXT>
